    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m parting ways with my trusty ride, and honestly, it\u2019s been such a joy to drive. It\u2019s in really solid shape and has clearly been well-loved over the years. Whether you're commuting or heading out on a road trip, this car is totally ready to hit the road! I've taken great care of it, and I'm looking for someone who will enjoy it as much as I have. Feel free to reach out with any questions\u2014I'd love to see it go to a good home!",
      "price": 29500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 31
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54B32 naturally aspirated 3.2L inline-six. This high-revving power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power to the rear wheels via a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable differential lock. The chassis remains taut with upgraded bushings, and the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced\u2014a critical preventative measure for this platform. While the exterior shows minor road patina consistent with its age, the powertrain remains robust, exhibiting strong compression and smooth delivery through the entire 8,000 RPM range. Recent service includes a comprehensive valve clearance adjustment and a cooling system overhaul featuring a high-flow water pump.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 31
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used car in good condition. Regularly maintained. Clean title. Minor interior wear. Runs smooth.",
      "price": 31500.0,
